  "summary": "Binary columnar storage for TPC-H SF10 analytical workload. Hot tables (lineitem, orders, customer) sorted by frequently-filtered columns (l_shipdate, o_orderdate, c_custkey) with zone maps on 100K-row blocks for predicate pushdown. Low-cardinality strings (flags, statuses, segments) use dictionary encoding (uint8_t/uint16_t). Sorted indexes on l_shipdate and o_orderdate enable range query optimization; hash indexes on join keys (l_orderkey, o_custkey, c_custkey, c_mktsegment) accelerate joins. Cold tables (part, partsupp, supplier, nation, region) stored without indexes—loaded on demand for join operations. Parallel ingestion via global thread pool across all tables, per-column buffered writes, permutation-based sorting for lineitem and orders. Date values encoded as days since Unix epoch (1970-01-01) for correct range filtering."
